helpdesk-note.body:
Hello Logan!
Thank you for reaching out regarding having issues with accessing the application.
I have looked for your account and noticed you did not have one on the www.msoe.edu site. This could be why it was difficult to reset a password. I am sorry for the inconvenience you have experienced.
You may apply to MSOE by using this link: http://start.msoe.edu/applynow/inquiryform An account on the MSOE community is no longer required for application, though we certainly encourage you to consider creating one. The community will provide the opportunity to interact with admission counselors, future classmates and learn more about what it will be like to be an MSOE student.
To create an MSOE Community account, please do the following:
Go to: https://community.msoe.edu/external-register.jspa Click on I AM NEW TO MSOE Complete information requested. Click CONTINUE
You will receive an activation email. Please click on the link provided in the email to complete your site registration. If you do not see the email, please check your spam or junk folder.
Please let me know if you have any questions. Thank you again for your patience.
Sincerely, Dana Grennier MSOE
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hello Logan!

Thank you for reaching out regarding having issues with accessing the application.

I have looked for your account and noticed you did not have one on the www.msoe.edu site.  This could be why it was difficult to reset a password.  I am sorry for the inconvenience you have experienced.

You may apply to MSOE by using this link: http://start.msoe.edu/applynow/inquiryform  An account on the MSOE community is no longer required for application, though we certainly encourage you to consider creating one.  The community will provide the opportunity to interact with admission counselors, future classmates and learn more about what it will be like to be an MSOE student.

To create an MSOE Community account, please do the following:
Go to: https://community.msoe.edu/external-register.jspa
Click on I AM NEW TO MSOE
Complete information requested.
Click CONTINUE

You will receive an activation email.  Please click on the link provided in the email to complete your site registration.  If you do not see the email, please check your spam or junk folder.

Please let me know if you have any questions. Thank you again for your patience.

Sincerely,
Dana Grennier
MSOE

Hi Helpdesk,
1. We are getting an authentication failure message before any spinning wheel/timed out message like we got before.
2. I haven’t seen one person able to print from the black and white printer today.
3. We have had multiple students and staff try to print with the same authentication failed message so it is not isolated to a person.
That being the case, I don’t feel like this ticket should be labeled as resolved.
Students can print black and white from the newly fixed color printer, though, so there is a work around now, but it is slower, the paper capacity is smaller, and the ink more expensive so this is not a perfect solution.
Please keep this ticket open.
Thank you,
Sarah Rowell, MLIS Librarian I MSOE Walter Schroeder Library 414-277-7180 rowell@msoe.edu<mailto:rowell@msoe.edu>

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Access Point Issue
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Matthew is unable to connect to his internet at home. Receives an access point error.
Search "Internet Options" in the Start menu. Select connections>LAN settings. Make sure only the Automatically detect settings box is checked.
Next search "Network and Sharing Center". Select Change Adapter Settings. For both the wired and wireless icons, right click and open properties. Under the "This connection uses the following items:" double click on Internet Protocol 6 and verify the settings are set to automatically detect settings. Do the same for Internet Protocol 4.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Matthew is unable to connect to his internet at home. Receives an access point error.

Search "Internet Options" in the Start menu. Select connections>LAN settings. Make sure only the Automatically detect settings box is checked.

Next search "Network and Sharing Center". Select Change Adapter Settings. For both the wired and wireless icons, right click and open properties. Under the "This connection uses the following items:" double click on Internet Protocol 6 and verify the settings are set to automatically detect settings. Do the same for Internet Protocol 4.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Elise Coleman,
This generally happens after updating your password. The solution is as follows:
1. Open the Start Menu. 2. Type in "Credential Manager" to the search bar. 3. Open the program called "Credential Manager" in the search results 4. In the bottom of the window, under Generic Credentials, you should see at least one with "Outlook" in the name. Click this credential and click the "Remove from Vault" option. 5. Confirm that you would like to remove the credential. 6. Re-open Outlook.
Please let me know if these steps work for you. Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/3398

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi afshan, Pat Hurlbut did some looking into this and found some similar issues people were having in discussion boards. A common issue is that the laptop you are using is running on battery power, and it is trying to save power by not sending as much to the projector. Honestly, we are not sure if this is what you have been running into, but it may be.
If you haven't been already, try plugging the laptop in while you are presenting to see if that helps. If not, please let us know and we will try something else. We will do what we can to make this work correctly for you.
Thanks for your patience.
Sincerely,
Andrew Holmes Instructional Technology

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Judah Balli, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/3473 My password is expired and Iam unable to reset.
Due to the current server outages it is difficult for us to reset your password for you. However, if you are going to be on campus there is a simple, easy solution for you. All you need to do is plug your MSOE laptop into the domain via an ethernet cable, then hit CTRL+ALT+DELETE ---> Change a Password. Following those steps will change your password on the domain, even if your password has expired. Feel free to come to the Helpdesk at the CC and we can help you with this.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mark Cribb,
According to our records your password has been expired for ~6 months. Due to a current server outage we are unable to simply reset it for you. If you are going to be on campus, you simply need to connect to the domain with an ethernet cable, hit CTRL+ALT+DELETE---> Change a Password. This will allow you to change your password to something of your choosing. You do need to know the old password though. If you are not going to be on campus soon, we will need information from you so that we know that you are, in fact, Mark Cribb. If this is the case you will need to contact us at 414-277-7288. Have a great day!

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi chanc, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/3556
Blackboard is still working, however, the login process is a little different. You can go to the login screen as you normally would, however, once, you are at the login page under the login button there should be something that says "MSOE SSO" which you should click on. A new login page should appear in which you can enter your login. Please be aware the new login page uses an email address for login instead of your username. If you could let us know if this solves your problem it would be greatly apprecaited.
Thanks,
Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Blackboard and VPN
helpdesk-ticket.description:
You probably already know this and if it is part of a widespread, known problem there is no need for you create a ticket for it...
I can't get VPN to connect. The system just keeps asking for my password.
I can't log into Blackboard. I get stuck on the single signing screen.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
You probably already know this and if it is part of a widespread, known problem there is no need for you create a ticket for it…
 
I can’t get VPN to connect. The system just keeps asking for my password.
 
I can’t log into Blackboard. I get stuck on the single signing screen.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Charles Tritt,
There is a known issue with GlobalProtect (sslvpn.msoe.edu) not authenticating correctly at the moment. However, blackboard does still work (with a minor work-around).
if you go to msoe.blackboard.com and instead of typing your username and password into the sign-on fields, click on "Sign on using MSOE SSO" underneath the sign-on fields. Then enter your email and password, and vuola, you should be able to get in. Please let others know.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Katie, I think that Andy or I could help you make the connection, but we need to see it from your login view. I'm off on Monday, but will ask Andy to reach out to you and see if he can help with the link. McGraw also has their own support contacts, and sometimes it's helpful to call them too - they can describe what information they actually need for the link. We do have Blackboard set up behind the scenes to accept Connect materials, so I think it's a matter of matching your text with their site materials using the Course Tools menu in the lower left menu, and then it will let you pull materials into the content areas.
